Farming hurts lower level players.<br>
It saddens me to see a level 20 player unable to take a shot at acquiring something they need simply because a level 50 player is sitting on the spawn in order to farm for cash.<br>
<br>
Personally I'd rather miss out on a needed item that drops from a green than to see that happen, as long as it doesn't interfere with quests.<br>
<br>
And honestly, from all I've seen in my time playing EverQuest, I think that players going after green mobs for needed items is rather rare. As a rule players tend to froth at the bit to get REALLY wanted items...and usually attempt to get them BEFORE thier appropriate level whenever possible.<br>
<br>
<br>
I just can't see profit being placed before need in a game like this.<br>
If most people that played EverQuest placed honor and morals before personal gain, restrictive rules wouldn't be needed.<br>
But we all know that this is not how things truly are.<br>
<br>
I can see where honest roleplaying might be a reason to behave otherwise, but I don't think anyone can kid themselves into believing that Norrath contains more than a tiny percentage of actual roleplayers.<br>
<br>
Right or wrong, that's my view...and it won't change.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Happy Gaming,<br>
Orv<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 2:23:21 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/concussion.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A better way to implement Loot Rules</span><hr size=1> No-Drop Lore tags would do nothing. If an item is worth camping, people will camp it one way or another.<br>
<br>
Here's a perfect example. Skyshrine. Guardian Armor is all Lore and No-drop, yet it's farmed all the time by high levels. They'll either:<br>
<br>
A) Solo their high levels in safe areas, where they can later run in their twink if something drops.<br>
<br>
B) Play on two computers, with two accounts. You'd be surprised how many people play two accounts at the same time.<br>
<br>
C) Group with lowbies and role for the drops. This only happens rarely, and to tell the truth, is probably the best solution.<br>
<br>
So, how would you keep people from doing A or B, and try to get them to do C?<br>
<br>
So far we've seen a few ways to limit who goes where:<br>
<br>
Level Limits - Planes so far are the only zones I can think of that work off this.<br>
<br>
Keys - Keys are a great way to either make a sucessful dungeon (Sebilis) or an empty farmland (ToFS).<br>
<br>
Warrens Loot Code - So far, Warrens, Stonebrunt, oh, and all of Luclin. It seems to me that this has exactly the same effect as making a zone all No-Drop/Lore. Farmers can still get twink items. They just have to be a little careful with their Twinks.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think they need a new tag for items. Something like an Artifact, in that you (personally) can only ever have one. In other words, you get one. If you trade it, sell it, drop it, or use it for a quest, it's gone for good. No-Way to get it back.<br>
This would destroy farming, and allow items to be traded. Since items could only be obtained once, they'd not be treated like currency.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying all items should be tagged like this. Just the ones that VI would normally institute the WLC for. <p><center><IMG SRC=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/jarnin3dsig.jpg><br><center><Br><Br>Grand Master Fisherman<Br>Master Brewer<Br>Master Chef<Br>Master of Begging<Br><Br><b>DEATH TO AL`KABOR!</b></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6698.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6331.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=6686.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=6686.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6686.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6686.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option v